{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"95028cca-5bd8-47b6-a5d5-9c55a27cfa99","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Waiting on bug fix #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Waiting on bug fix #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\n> **Note:** For xUnit `[Theory]` tests, use `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` instead of `[Fact]`. In all frameworks, providing a reason string is recommended so skipped tests show up clearly in test reports.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d25980be-5b4e-4eaa-b149-d638114cebd9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":323,"requestId":"0C0D:1EBB02:56A551:64EE53:69F009AF"},"id":"bb536a71-f3c1-4cd1-9334-db9468eae780","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:13:25.699Z","parentId":"39c4b84c-8d75-44e6-b837-8c3cf247927c"}
